{"config_id": "v1-current", "question_id": "Q1", "tier": "basic", "question": "What is the capital income tax rate (pääomatulovero) applicable to the portion of capital income that exceeds 30,000 euros in a tax year?", "gold_answer": "The capital income tax rate applicable to the portion of capital income exceeding 30,000 euros in a tax year is 34%. Capital income up to 30,000 euros is taxed at the lower rate of 30%.", "gold_key_facts": ["The capital income tax rate applicable to the portion of capital income exceeding 30,000 euros in a tax year is 34%.", "Capital income up to 30,000 euros is taxed at the lower rate of 30%."], "gold_citation_publishers": ["vero"], "answer_result": {"question": "What is the capital income tax rate (pääomatulovero) applicable to the portion of capital income that exceeds 30,000 euros in a tax year?", "answer": "The capital income tax rate on the portion of capital income exceeding 30,000 euros is 34 percent [Source 2][Source 8]. This is the *pääomatulon korotettu tuloveroprosentti* (increased tax rate for capital income) [Source 2]. The rate applies to the amount exceeding the 30,000-euro threshold, while the portion up to 30,000 euros is taxed at 30 percent [Source 2][Source 5]. The same rates are confirmed in the *Verohallinto* decision for 2026 [Source 1].\n\nHuomioitavaa: [Source 3] reflects a temporary 33-percent rate for 2018, which is no longer in force. [Source 4], [Source 6], and [Source 7] contain historical thresholds and rates (40,000/32% and 50,000/32%) that have been superseded by the current 30,000/34% rule.", "cited_source_ids": ["finlex/laki/finlex-laki-laki-tuloverolain-muuttamisesta-24-html-a2db51c4/s124#0", "finlex/laki/finlex-laki-laki-rajoitetusti-verovelvollisen-tulon-verottamisesta-annetun-lain-40e9c464/s15#0", "vero/vero_paatos/vero-syventavat-vero-ohjeet-paatokset-verohallinnon-paatos-luonnollisille-henkil-9f9a4821/c1/s1-3/s1-3-1/s1-3-1-2#0", "vero/vero_paatos/vero-syventavat-vero-ohjeet-paatokset-verohallinn